  <h1>Data Sources</h1>  

  <p>Bill Track is an <a href="/open-source">open source</a> project that garners its information from a variety of other websites. Currently the site depends on the following sites:</p>

  <h2><a href="http://govtrack.us">GovTrack.us</a></h2>
  <p>
    GovTrack.us is a site powered by a series of xml file that have been meticulously engineered by Josh Tauberer. Although information is provided via an API, GovTrack.us also makes it's files available directly. These XML files are used on the site to build a relational database that connects politicians to their works. 
  </p>
  
  <h2><a href="http://sunlightlabs.com">Sunlight Labs</a></h2>
  <p>
    Sunlight Labs, in addition to being the inspiration for creating this application, provides a information via an excellent API. They provide this website with the foundational information on politicians and districts.
  </p> 
  
  
  <h2><a href="http://congress.mcommons.com/">Mobile Commons</a></h2> 
